              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "SYNCH"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAANL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " IPNS - Intense Pulsed Neutron Source,",
                "the first spallation slow neutron source based on a",
                "proton synchrotron."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Fe foil packets were 2.5 cm in diameter and the",
                "foils varied from 0.025 to 0.5 mm thick. Foil packets",
                "were suspended on a network of thin aluminum rods at",
                "angles of 0, 7.5, 30, 60, 90, 120, and 150 degrees."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "TOF",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Activation rates were measured in",
                "Fe foils at well-defined geometry in neutron fields",
                "created by 113 and 256 MeV proton beams in thick Al",
                "and U targets. The neutron spectra were independently",
                "measured using time-of-flight spectrometry. Following",
                "irradiations, the foil packets were retrieved and",
                "individual foils were analyzed by gamma spectroscopy.",
                "Comparison of these data sets provides integral",
                "testing and some adjusting of the poorly known",
                "activation cross sections at higher energies. 54Mn,",
                "51Cr, 52Mn cross sections obtained by adjustment of",
                "prior cross sections."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The foil activation measurements were",
                "converted to activation rates with suitable",
                "corrections for gamma self-absorption and decay",
                "during and after irradiation. We assume that",
                "reactions that agree within 20% with integral testing",
                "should not be adjusted. Considerable effort is",
                "required to understand all sources of uncertainty, as",
                "well as their covariances, and to accurately take",
                "into account biases in the measurement techniques",
                "produced by geometric differences between",
                "time-of-flight and foil arrangements as well as",
                "neutron scattering effects. This work was focused on",
                "reaction cross sections that have large disagreements",
                "in integral testing."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "date": 20170412,
                "history": "C"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " BP"
              ]
            }
          ],
